HEADWORD: Fumed oak
<hw>Fumed oak</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Cabinetwork)</fld> <def>Oak given
a weathered appearance by exposure in an air-tight compartment to fumes
of ammonia from uncorked cans, being first given a coat of
filler.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fumeless</ent>⟦br⟧
